# TrailVerse (NPE-USA) — Master Context

## Product

**TrailVerse** (production: [nationalparksexplorerusa.com](https://www.nationalparksexplorerusa.com)) is a national-parks exploration and trip-planning product covering **470+ NPS parks and sites**.

- **Brand voice**: "Your Universe of National Parks Exploration"
- **AI persona**: **Trailie** — park trip planner (nav label "Trailie", routes under `/plan-ai`)
- **Public value prop**: Real-time weather, maps, reviews, compare, events, discover-by-taxonomy, blog, and AI itineraries — **no account required** to browse parks

## Repository layout

```
npe-usa/
├── package.json          # Root: `npm run dev` runs frontend + backend via concurrently
├── next-frontend/        # Next.js App Router (primary UI) — Node 20, v0.4.0, Next 16.x
├── server/               # Express API + MongoDB + Socket.IO
├── mcp-server/           # TrailVerse MCP for Claude/ChatGPT integrations
└── docs/                 # SEO, content-engine, plans (not runtime)
```

## Local development

| Service | Command | URL |
|---------|---------|-----|
| Both | `npm run dev` (repo root) | — |
| Frontend only | `cd next-frontend && npm run dev` | http://127.0.0.1:3000 |
| Backend only | `cd server && npm run dev` | http://localhost:5001/api |

- Frontend proxies `/api/*` and `/uploads/*` to backend (`next-frontend/next.config.mjs` rewrites)
- Default API base: `http://127.0.0.1:5001/api` via `getApiBaseUrl()` in `next-frontend/src/lib/apiBase.js`
- Production API: `https://trailverse.onrender.com/api`

## Tech stack

| Layer | Choices |
|-------|---------|
| Frontend | Next.js App Router, React 19, Tailwind v4, TanStack Query, Phosphor icons (`@components/icons`), Serwist PWA |
| Backend | Express, Mongoose, JWT auth, Socket.IO, Swagger at `/api-docs` |
| Data | MongoDB; NPS API; OpenWeather; Google Maps (server proxy); RIDB; GTFS transit |
| AI | OpenAI + Anthropic (Plan AI / Trailie) |
| Email | Resend (primary) |
| Deploy | Vercel (frontend), Render (backend) |

## Global frontend providers (`next-frontend/src/components/Providers.jsx`)

- `QueryClientProvider` (5min staleTime)
- `ThemeProvider` — CSS vars: `--bg-primary`, `--text-primary`, `--accent-green`, `--font-display`
- `AuthProvider` — JWT in cookie `trailverse_auth_token` + localStorage patterns via `authService`
- `ToastProvider`, Vercel Analytics/Speed Insights, Serwist SW (production only)
- Root layout adds `VoiceButton` (Talk to Trailie), `GoogleMapsLoader`

## Middleware / proxy (`next-frontend/src/proxy.js`)

- **Protected** (no cookie → `/login?redirect=...`): `/profile`, `/chat-history`, `/dashboard`, `/settings`, `/home` (no `/plan-ai/new` page — unified chat at `/plan-ai`)
- **Auth-only redirect** (logged in → `/home`): `/login`, `/signup`, `/forgot-password`, `/reset-password`
- **Blog slug redirects**: fetches `/api/blogs/slug-redirects`, 308 to canonical slug

## SEO conventions

- **Canonical domain**: `https://www.nationalparksexplorerusa.com`
- **Indexable**: use `indexablePageRobots` from `@/lib/seo`
- **Private** (noindex): auth, profile, admin, chat-history, shared trips — use `privatePageRobots` / `privatePageMetadata`
- **Park URLs**: slug-based `/parks/{full-name-slug}` (e.g. `yellowstone-national-park`); short codes redirect via `next.config.mjs`
- **Sitemap**: `next-frontend/src/app/sitemap.ts` — static + parks + states + blogs + guides + intent landings
- **robots.txt**: disallows `/admin`, `/login`, `/profile`, `/plan-ai/shared/`, etc.

## Park slug system

- Source of truth: `next-frontend/src/data/park-slugs.json` (generated prebuild)
- Utils: `next-frontend/src/utils/parkSlug.js` — `parkToSlug`, `findCorrectSlug`
- Redirect: `/parks/yell` → `/parks/yellowstone-national-park` (permanent)

## When changing code

1. **Match existing patterns** — JSX (not TS) in frontend; Express controllers + services on backend
2. **Minimize scope** — parks/discover/SEO are sensitive; test slug redirects and metadata
3. **API calls from browser** — prefer relative `/api/...` (rewritten) or `getApiBaseUrl()`
4. **Auth** — `Authorization: Bearer` from cookie; `optionalAuth` for likes/reviews
5. **Do not** commit secrets, `.env`, or large SEO export zips in repo root

